title: mismatched receipt headers for block  (mainnet)
body:
I was synched for a couple of weeks on mainnet.  I did a git pull yesterday, recompiled.  Restarted.  Unfortunately this showed up...

```
WARN[09-07|02:08:07.996] [7/16 Execution] Execution failed        block=15467164 hash=0xa7d63c7dcce3ef22de66b0c8977b83f6e447f1d2bb0930ff24a6b889ce2416c2 err="mismatched receipt headers for block 15467164 (0xc1fc420cdf01e5723d8329cc2ddbf9402cffa04739ff3a75b0b7fba208d87cdd != 0xe0481543f8d100763ab0c0843fcdc6d2c26534a76c153eb61f8a04a82cdbc3d8)"
EROR[09-07|02:08:10.778] Staged Sync                              err="must not happen, ResetSequence: 1729458141, lastInDB: 1729458141, trace: [stageloop.go:136 panic.go:844 accessors_chain.go:855 stage_bodies.go:306 default_stages.go:78 sync.go:384 sync.go:223 stageloop.go:170 stageloop.go:91 asm_amd64.s:1571]"
```
I attempted to switch to a build from "stable", but that did not work.
Is there a way I can recover this?

#### System information

Erigon version: `erigon version 2022.08.3-alpha-488121f6`

OS & Version: 
```
DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu
DISTRIB_RELEASE=20.04
DISTRIB_CODENAME=focal
DISTRIB_DESCRIPTION="Ubuntu 20.04.4 LTS"
```
